'''Lily van den Broecke''' (born on 8 January 1992) is a British rower who is scheduled to compete at the [[2012 Summer Paralympics]] as the [[coxswain (rowing)|coxswain]] for the British four.

==Personal life==
Lily van den Broecke was born on 8 January 1992 in [[London]], England.<ref name=bpa>{{cite web|title=Lily van den Broecke|url=http://www.paralympics.org.uk/gb/athletes/lily-van-den-broecke|publisher=British Paralympic Association|accessdate=26 August 2012}}</ref> 

She is a student at [[Durham University]] where she is studying for a [[Bachelor of Arts]] degree in politics.<ref>{{cite web|title=Lily van den Broecke Biography|url=http://www.dur.ac.uk/news/torch/lily/|publisher=Durham University News|accessdate=26 August 2012}}</ref> 

==Rowing==
She began rowing when she attended [[Headington School, Oxford]]. After competing in [[sculling]] for four years she tried out as a [[coxswain (rowing)|cox]]. In 2009 she coxed the junior women's eight crew to fouth place at the [[Australian Youth Olympic Festival]] and a gold medal at the [[Coupe de la Jeunesse]] in [[Vichy]], France. In 2010 she won a gold medal coxing the junior women's eight at the [[World Rowing Junior Championships]] in [[Racice]], Czech Republic.<ref name=bpa/>

In 2011 she competed at the at [[2011 World Rowing Championships|World Rowing Championships]] held at [[Lake Bled]], [[Bled]], Slovenia. She won a gold medal in the LTAMix4+ event coxing a crew of [[Pam Relph]], [[Naomi Riches]], [[James Roe (rower)|James Roe]] and [[David Smith (rower)|David Smith]].<ref name=bpa/><ref>{{cite news|title=World Rowing: GB mixed coxed four win adaptive gold|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/disability-sport/14781065|accessdate=25 August 2012|date=4 September 2011|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> They completed the one kilometre course in a time of three minutes, 27.10 seconds, finishing nearly five seconds ahead of runners-up Canada. The result qualified a boat for Great Britain into the [[2012 Summer Paralympics]] in [[London]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Wham, bam thank you Pam as rower gets gold to set up London 2012 dream|url=http://www.bucksherald.co.uk/sport/other-sports/wham_bam_thank_you_pam_as_rower_gets_gold_to_set_up_london_2012_dream_1_3039686|accessdate=25 August 2012|newspaper=The Bucks Herald|date=8 September 2011}}</ref>  The crew repeated their gold medal result at the Munich World Cup event in 2012.<ref name=bpa/>

She has been selected to cox the crew of Relph, Riches, Roe and Smith in the [[Rowing at the 2012 Summer Paralympics - Mixed coxed four|mixed coxed four]] event for [[Great Britain at the 2012 Summer Paralympics]].<ref>{{cite news|title=London 2012: Lily Van den Broecke joy at selection|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/olympics/18609000|accessdate=26 August 2012|date=27 June 2012|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> <ref>{{cite news|title=2012 Paralympics: GB rowing's mixed coxed four - who's who?|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/disability-sport/18968710|accessdate=25 August 2012|date=25 August 2012|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> The event is scheduled to take place between 31 August and 2 September at [[Eton Dorney]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mixed Coxed Four - LTAMix4+|url=http://www.london2012.com/paralympics/rowing/event/mixed-coxed-four-ltamix4/|publisher=The London Organising Committee of the Olympic Games and Paralympic Games Limited|accessdate=25 August 2012}}</ref>

